The article is a statement from the President of the United States condemning the brutal murder of UK citizen Alan Henning by the terrorist group ISIL. Henning was known for his efforts to improve the lives of the Syrian people. The President expresses his condolences to Henning's family and the people of the United Kingdom. He also vows to work with the UK and other allies to bring the perpetrators of Henning's murder, as well as the murders of Jim Foley, Steven Sotloff, and David Haines, to justice. The President reiterates the commitment to taking decisive action to degrade and ultimately destroy ISIL.